values: Today is the day that is my first time writing in my live journal.  I am soooo excited to be able to write down what I have been doing up here in UW Oshkosh.  Here we go...Today I woke up at 8:00am and then took a shower.  I had to be at an OT appointment at 9:15, so I left a little earlier so I could drop something off at reeve union to send something out ( I wonder who I sent it too) I don't know if you get a package maybe it was you??? Then I arrived 15 minuets earlier but oh well. I talked about how school was going and how I am doing in my classes...and thanks for asking I am doing great in my classes I like all of my teachers and classes all except one Modern Social Problem... (I think I am going to DROP it) My math teacher is funny, because he is really mean to people in class but really nice outside of class. (But I think there is something wrong with his mind; I will tell you more when I find out what)  Tonight I going to see some stupid play called A Piece o My Heart.  It starts at 7:00 and is and hour and a half long. I think I am going to show up for a bit of it then leave.  Also tonight is Real Life at 8:00 so I am going to that when the play gets done or when I leave.  Oh yeah how could I for get I read in the bible Genesis 1 and it was about how God created the earth.  I took out a quote for the chapter and here it is..."In the beginning, when God created the heavens and the earth, the earth was a formless wasteland, and darkness covered the abyss, while a mighty wind swept over the waters."  It showed me that no matter how things look in the beginning how bad or good they can always change to how you want it to be. God choose to change how the earth we live in to something useful.  He had very little in his favor but manage to grow living things and make it a better place then what it was in the beginning.  So that means you have that same choice to change something back to good.
